definition: to add/to attach/to be close to/to be attached

sentences.english: You can also specify addendum terms or documentation.
sentences.chinese: 您還可以指定附錄條款或文檔。

sentences.english: Two or more addendums refer to the same business process.
sentences.chinese: 兩個或更多附錄引用了同一個業務流程。

sentences.english: I mean an addendum which he called postscript.
sentences.chinese: 我的意思是是他叫做補充說明的附錄。

sentences.english: In the end the thesis brings some appendixes relative to the system.
sentences.chinese: 文章最後還給出了與系統有關的一些有意義的附錄。

sentences.english: From my experience, it's best to make the assessment and the appendices separate artifacts.
sentences.chinese: 按照我的經驗，最好把評估和附錄分開。

sentences.english: Please quote for the subject item as per Annexure "A".
sentences.chinese: 請把這款產品的報價作爲附錄“A”。

sentences.english: Meanwhile, the advice on extracurricular reading materials is brought up in excursus.
sentences.chinese: 同時在附錄部分還提出了“關於課外讀物建議”。

sentences.english: See "Structure Limits" in Appendix D for details.
sentences.chinese: 詳細信息請參考附錄D中的”結構限制”。

sentences.english: Detong, post it under Appendix 1 of Bath Pond book.
sentences.chinese: 茶桶，將此上傳至《浴塘遊詠》的附錄一中。

sentences.english: Read the text in Appendix 3 (Immunological Computation by Dipankar Dasgupta and Louis Fernando Niño).
The appendix enquiries into the author of Tao Wu Xian Ping who was not Li Qing .
sentences.chinese: 附錄對《檮杌閒評》作者非李清說作了考辨。

sentences.english: Flashlights are not listed explicitly in Annex IB of the WEEE Directive.
sentences.chinese: WEEE指令附錄IB中沒有明確列出閃光燈。

sentences.english: The QS regulation is reprinted in the appendix of this manual.
sentences.chinese: 在本手冊的附錄中重印了質量體系法規。

sentences.english: Data of firefighting and lifesaving, see Annex F.
sentences.chinese: 設施消防救生設備的有關資料，參見附錄F。

sentences.english: Appendix contains Linying dialect vocabulary and classification of recorded sound corpus.
sentences.chinese: 附錄包含有臨潁方言分類詞表和語料記音。

sentences.english: She added a codicil to her will just before she died.
sentences.chinese: 臨終前在遺囑上加了附錄。

definition: variant of 匯編|汇编[hui4 bian1]
catalog/table of contents/directory (on computer hard drive)/list/contents
to annotate/to add marginal comments on/criticism/marginalia
to include (in a collection)/to put together (stories, poems etc)/to record/to employ/to recruit
entire book/unabridged book/entire multi-volume work/comprehensive volume
marginal notes/annotation/to annotate/to add comments to text
